title: Appointments to Expert Committee on Food Safety
content_text: The Secretary for Food and Health, Professor Sophia Chan, said that food safety was one of the priorities of the Government, and that she looked to the Expert Committee for advice to the Director of Food and Environmental Hygiene (DFEH) on matters relating to food safety. Professor Chan thanked the outgoing Chairman, Professor Ma Ching-yung, and seven outgoing members, namely Professor Chen Junshi, Ms Sylvia Chung Wai-man, Professor Vincent Lee Hon-leung, Mr Anthony Lock Kwok-on, Professor Chris Wong Kong-chu, Ms Jaime Wong Shuk-fong and Ms Rosa Wong Wan-ming, for their invaluable contributions to the

Jaime Wong Shuk-fong and Ms Rosa Wong Wan-ming, for their invaluable contributions to the work of the Expert Committee in the past.   The Expert Committee advises the DFEH on existing or new food safety operational strategies and measures to protect public health. It also advises the DFEH on standards or guidelines relating to food safety and food composition having regard to international practices, trends and developments.
